  <entry>
    <title>checkout, revert, restore, reset</title>
    <link href="http://example.com/2021/05/26/checkout_revert_restore_reset/"/>
    <id>http://example.com/2021/05/26/checkout_revert_restore_reset/</id>
    <published>2021-05-26T02:14:28.000Z</published>
    <updated>2021-05-26T05:36:19.429Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<blockquote><p>如果时光可以倒流,你会怎么样? 我相信每个人的人生选择都将会不同,至少你不会再做出现在来看是错误的选择.<br>在代码的世界里,版本管理工具给你反悔的机会.</p></blockquote><h5 id="Git中存在的几个区域"><a href="#Git中存在的几个区域" class="headerlink" title="Git中存在的几个区域:"></a>Git中存在的几个区域:</h5><p><img src="/images/git_revert_reset_restore.png" alt="this is an image"> </p><p>不难git这样设计的目的,一个类似于平行宇宙的概念,他不是简单的备份,而且git追踪的是变化,而不是文件本身. git 中被tracking的文件, 就是在不断的从一个区移到另外一个区,同时文件的状态,被标识为不同的状态.</p><blockquote><p>比如:git add指令会把working里面的所有文件,“移动“到staged区,同时working里面所有untracked的文件转换为staged.</p></blockquote><p>我们可以逻辑上,把git里面的文件抽象为以下几种状态,其实这样划分严格意义上并不是很准确,只是方便理解.</p><h5 id="Git中文件抽象为以下几种状态及其对应区域"><a href="#Git中文件抽象为以下几种状态及其对应区域" class="headerlink" title="Git中文件抽象为以下几种状态及其对应区域:"></a>Git中文件抽象为以下几种状态及其对应区域:</h5><ul><li><code>untracked</code> :文件不受git “追踪”的状态,对应working区,你修改后的文件,如果没有add,commit,最开始就是在working区.不难理解working就是当前工作区.</li><li><code>modified</code>  :git ”追踪“到已经修改,对应working区.</li><li><code>staged</code>   :git已经暂存,对应staged区.</li><li><code>commited</code> :git已经提交,对应repository区.</li></ul><p><strong>git命令每次执行完毕, 都会反馈给你一些信息,这些信息包含了,当前分支,文件状态,已经当前命令的回撤和进一步操作的info.你读懂了会发现其实命令行界面也可以用户体验很好.</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br><span class="line">12</span><br><span class="line">13</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"># untracking</span><br><span class="line">duke@MacBook-Pro GitStudy % git status</span><br><span class="line">On branch master</span><br><span class="line">Changes not staged for commit:</span><br><span class="line">  (use &quot;git add &lt;file&gt;...&quot; to update what will be committed)</span><br><span class="line">  (use &quot;git restore &lt;file&gt;...&quot; to discard changes in working directory)</span><br><span class="line">    modified:   hello.txt</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">Untracked files:</span><br><span class="line">  (use &quot;git add &lt;file&gt;...&quot; to include in what will be committed)</span><br><span class="line">    &quot;hello\347\232\204\345\211\257\346\234\254.txt&quot;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">no changes added to commit (use &quot;git add&quot; and/or &quot;git commit -a&quot;)</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><blockquote><p>所以我们知道了,git 命令其实就是让git中tracking的文件, 从一个区“到”另外一个区,同时伴随着文件的状态从一个状态切换到另外一个状态.<br>其实我们人生活中地点的变化也往往伴随着身份的变化,当我们从家里到公司,身份从儿子/丈夫到工程师.我们从淘宝买的东西,快递在仓库是未发货状态,接着伴随地点的变化,状态变为分拣,运输中,最后到你手里,你确认收货,那就是签收状态了.</p></blockquote><p>如果搞清楚了git中文件的几种状态,就可以看看git中几条让时光逆转的几条指令.</p><h5 id="几条时光逆转的指令"><a href="#几条时光逆转的指令" class="headerlink" title="几条时光逆转的指令"></a>几条时光逆转的指令</h5><ol><li><code>git checkout</code></li><li><code>git restore</code></li><li><code>git revert</code></li><li><code>git reset</code></li></ol><p>文件在git中分为不同的状态,以上几条指令可以在不同的状态下切换,达到回退的目的.<br><strong>具体详细的使用请执行:git help</strong></p><blockquote><p><code>git checkout</code> 让staged区文件back到working区.覆盖当前working区,从而达到回退目的.git restore 也可以达到目的, 每次add命令执行完毕,都会给出反馈: (use “git restore <file>…” to discard changes in working directory).就是这个意思.</p></blockquote><blockquote><p><code>git restore</code> 除了可以让你放弃当前working区的更改,还可以把文件从staged区back到working区.但是文件的改动此时依然存在.</p></blockquote><p><strong>使用restore命令,放弃working区更改&amp;把staged区文件back到working区</strong>:</p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br><span class="line">12</span><br><span class="line">13</span><br><span class="line">14</span><br><span class="line">15</span><br><span class="line">16</span><br><span class="line">17</span><br><span class="line">18</span><br><span class="line">19</span><br><span class="line">20</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">duke@MacBook-Pro GitStudy % git status</span><br><span class="line">On branch master</span><br><span class="line">Changes to be committed:</span><br><span class="line">  (use &quot;git restore --staged &lt;file&gt;...&quot; to unstage)</span><br><span class="line">    modified:   hello.txt</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">duke@MacBook-Pro GitStudy % git restore --staged hello.txt</span><br><span class="line">duke@MacBook-Pro GitStudy % git status</span><br><span class="line">On branch master</span><br><span class="line">Changes not staged for commit:</span><br><span class="line">  (use &quot;git add &lt;file&gt;...&quot; to update what will be committed)</span><br><span class="line">  (use &quot;git restore &lt;file&gt;...&quot; to discard changes in working directory)</span><br><span class="line">    modified:   hello.txt</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">no changes added to commit (use &quot;git add&quot; and/or &quot;git commit -a&quot;)</span><br><span class="line">duke@MacBook-Pro GitStudy % git restore hello.txt</span><br><span class="line">duke@MacBook-Pro GitStudy % git status</span><br><span class="line">On branch master</span><br><span class="line">nothing to commit, working tree clean</span><br><span class="line">duke@MacBook-Pro GitStudy % </span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><blockquote><p><code>git revert commit-id</code>, 针对repository区的commited 文件, 回退到上次committed,然后把当前回退的改动再次提交. 作为更改它是有记录,更安全.</p><p>如果你当前working区, 有改动你想revert,必须要先commit才能revert.</p></blockquote><p><strong>revert 报错</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">duke@MacBook-Pro GitStudy % git revert 3fb4844</span><br><span class="line">error: Your local changes to the following files would be overwritten by merge:</span><br><span class="line">    hello.txt</span><br><span class="line">Please commit your changes or stash them before you merge.</span><br><span class="line">Aborting</span><br><span class="line">fatal: revert failed</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><blockquote><p><code>git reset</code>,用来设置分支的头部指向,对应repository区里面有很多提交,使用git reset可以把当前提交重置到某次提交.<br>reset 有 –soft,–mixed,–hard可选.<br>当使用hard, 被回退的那些版本的修改会直接舍弃,commit-id所对应的提交直接会覆盖到working区, 此时不管working区里面的文件是什么状态,好像它们没有来过一样。其他的分别会回退到staged区和working区.</p></blockquote><p>总结:写的比较长.感觉还是有不够透彻的地方,凡事都要自己动手.</p>]]></content>
    
    
      
      
    <summary type="html">&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;如果时光可以倒流,你会怎么样? 我相信每个人的人生选择都将会不同,至少你不会再做出现在来看是错误的选择.&lt;br&gt;在代码的世界里,版本管理工具给你反悔的机会.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h5 id=&quot;Git中存在的几个区域&quot;&gt;&lt;a hre</summary>
      
    
    
    
